.SH DESCRIPTION
.B coda
is a shell-function toolkit that combines OpenCode AI agents, tmux persistent
sessions, and git worktrees into a single workflow.
Each project lives as a bare git repository with multiple worktrees — one per
branch — each with its own isolated OpenCode agent running in its own tmux session.
.PP
All functions are sourced into the shell from
.IR shell-functions.sh .
Configuration is read from
.I .env
in the same directory.
.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.
.SS Session management
.
.TP
.B coda \fR[\fIname\fR] [\fIdir\fR]
Attach to an existing tmux session or create a new one running
.BR opencode (1).
.I name
defaults to the basename of the current directory.
.I dir
defaults to the current directory.
Session names are prefixed with
.B SESSION_PREFIX
(default:
.IR coda- ).
Passing a name that already includes the prefix is safe — it is stripped
automatically.
If already inside tmux, switches to the session rather than creating a nested
attach.
.
.TP
.B coda ls
List all active
.B coda
sessions (those whose names match
.BR SESSION_PREFIX ).
.
.TP
.B coda switch
Open an interactive
.BR fzf (1)
picker showing all tmux sessions.
The right pane shows a live preview of the last 30 lines of each session.
Press
.B Enter
to switch; press
.B Esc
to cancel.
Also available as
.B prefix\~+\~f
inside tmux.
.
.SS Headless mode
.
.TP
.B coda serve \fR[\fIport\fR]
Start
.B opencode serve
on
.I port
(or the next free port starting at
.BR OPENCODE_BASE_PORT ).
The permission policy is taken from
.B OPENCODE_HEADLESS_PERMISSION
(default:
.IR \[lq]{\[dq]*\[dq]:\[dq]allow\[dq]}\[rq] ,
which auto-approves all actions).
.sp
Once running, attach a TUI with:
.RS
.EX
opencode attach http://localhost:\fIport\fP
.EE
.RE
or submit tasks programmatically via the OpenCode HTTP API.
.
.SS Authentication
.
.TP
.B coda auth
Install the
.B opencode-claude-auth
plugin globally, which lets OpenCode reuse the OAuth credentials written by
.BR "claude auth login"
to
.IR ~/.claude/.credentials.json .
Run once after
.BR "claude auth login" .
Re-run if Claude auth expires.
.
.SS Project management
.
.TP
.B coda project start
When run from inside a coda project directory (any worktree or the project
root), connects to an existing tmux session on the project's default branch
.RB ( main " or " master ).
If no active session is found, prints an error.
.
.TP
.B coda project start \-\-repo \fIurl\fR [\fIname\fR]
Clone
.I url
as a bare repository and create the initial
.B DEFAULT_BRANCH
worktree.
.I name
defaults to the repository basename.
The project is stored under
.IR PROJECTS_DIR / name /
with the following layout:
.RS
.EX
PROJECTS_DIR/name/
  .bare/        (all git objects)
  .git          (pointer: "gitdir: ./.bare")
  main/         (initial worktree)
.EE
.RE
If the project already exists, fetches the latest changes and shows current
worktrees instead.
.
.TP
.B coda project start \-\-new \fIrepo-name\fR [\fB\-\-message\fR|\fB\-m\fR \fIdescription\fR]
Create a new private repository under
.IR evanstern ,
bootstrap it from a local bare coda project, and push the initial commit.
.sp
If
.B \-\-message
is provided, the text is written to an
.B AGENTS.md
file in the repository root verbatim, intended as initial context for AI coding agents.
.sp
Requires the GitHub CLI
.RB ( gh )
to be installed and authenticated.
.
.TP
.B coda project close \fR[\fB\-\-delete\fR]
Close all active tmux sessions associated with the current project.
Must be run from inside a coda project directory (any worktree or the project
root).
.sp
By default, only tmux sessions are closed.
Use
.B \-\-delete
to also remove the entire project directory under
.BR PROJECTS_DIR ,
including the bare repository and all worktrees.
.sp
Teardown runs in a backgrounded subshell, so sessions or folders may take a
moment to disappear after the command returns.
.
.TP
.B coda project ls
List all coda-managed projects in
.BR PROJECTS_DIR .
.
.SS Feature worktrees
.
.TP
.B coda feature start \fIbranch\fR [\fIbase-branch\fR] [\fIproject-name\fR]
Create a new git worktree on a new branch and open an OpenCode tmux session
inside it.
Must be run from inside a project directory (any worktree or the project root).
.I base-branch
defaults to
.BR DEFAULT_BRANCH .
.I project-name
defaults to the project root directory basename.
.sp
If the worktree already exists, attaches to the existing session without
creating a duplicate.
.sp
Session name:
.IB SESSION_PREFIX project-name -- branch
.sp
Worktree path:
.IB PROJECTS_DIR / project / branch /
.
.TP
.B coda feature done \fIbranch\fR [\fIproject-name\fR]
Tear down a feature in three steps:
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Kill the tmux session.
.IP 2.
Remove the git worktree.
.IP 3.
Delete the local branch.
.RE
.sp
.B Warning:
the branch is deleted regardless of merge status.
Merge or push your changes before running this command.
.
.TP
.B coda feature finish \fR[\fB\-\-force\fR]
Agent-safe teardown of the current feature branch.
Detects the branch and project from the working directory (takes no arguments).
The teardown (kill session, remove worktree, delete branch) runs in a
backgrounded subshell so it completes even when called from within the session
being destroyed.
.sp
Refuses to proceed if there are uncommitted or untracked changes.
Use
.B \-\-force
to skip this check and tear down regardless.
.sp
Must be run from inside a feature worktree (not the default branch).
.
.TP
.B coda feature ls
Run
.B git worktree list
for the project root detected from the current directory.
.
.SS Tmux layouts
.
.TP
.B coda layout \fR[\fIname\fR]
Apply a tmux layout to the current session.
Creates new window(s) with the pane arrangement defined by the layout, all
starting in the session's base directory (the worktree root for feature
branches).
Equivalent to
.BR "coda layout apply" .
.sp
Must be run from inside a tmux session.
If the session was created by
.BR coda ,
the working directory is read from the
.B CODA_DIR
tmux environment variable; otherwise falls back to the current pane's path.
.
.TP
.B coda layout apply \fIname\fR
Explicit form of
.BR "coda layout" .
.
.TP
.B coda layout ls
List all available layouts from both the built-in
.I layouts/
directory and the user directory
.RB ( CODA_LAYOUTS_DIR ).
Shows the current default layout.
.
.TP
.B coda layout show \fIname\fR
Print the layout file contents, including the pane diagram and tmux commands.
.
.TP
.B coda layout create \fIname\fR
Create a new layout from a commented template in
.BR CODA_LAYOUTS_DIR .
The template includes example
.B tmux split-window
and
.B tmux send-keys
patterns for building custom pane arrangements.
.sp
Built-in layouts:
.RS
.TP
.B default
Single pane running
.BR opencode .
.TP
.B wide-twopane
Two side-by-side panes:
.B opencode
(left) and
.B nvim
(right).
.TP
.B classic
Single pane running
.BR opencode
(alias for the original behaviour).
.TP
.B three-pane
.B opencode
(top-left),
.B nvim
(top-right), shell (bottom).
.RE
.
.SS Session watcher
.
.TP
.B coda watch
.TQ
.B coda watch start
Start the background session watcher.
Polls all active
.B coda
sessions every
.B CODA_WATCH_INTERVAL
seconds (default: 5).
When an OpenCode instance finishes processing and begins waiting for input, the
watcher sends a terminal bell (BEL) to every attached tmux client and displays a
status-bar message identifying the session.
.sp
The bell propagates through mosh to your local terminal, which triggers an
OS-native notification (supported by Ghostty, iTerm2, Kitty, and most modern
terminal emulators).
.sp
The watcher runs in its own tmux session named
.BR coda-watcher .
.
.TP
.B coda watch stop
Stop the watcher by killing the
.B coda-watcher
tmux session.
.
.TP
.B coda watch status
Print whether the watcher is running and when it was started.
.
.SS Profiles
.
.TP
.B coda profile ls
List available profiles.
.
.TP
.B coda profile create \fIname\fR
Create a new profile in
.BR CODA_PROFILES_DIR .
Profiles are
.I .env
files that can override
.B CODA_LAYOUT
and
.BR CODA_NVIM_APPNAME .
.
.TP
.B coda profile show \fIname\fR
Print the contents of a profile.
.
.SS Help
.
.TP
.B coda help
Print a short usage summary.
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from
.I .env
in the
.B coda
directory (created from
.I .env.example
on first
.BR install.sh\ run ).
All variables can also be set in the environment before sourcing
.IR shell-functions.sh .
.
.TS
l l l.
Variable	Default	Description
_
PROJECTS_DIR	~/projects	Root dir for repos
SESSION_PREFIX	coda-	tmux session name prefix
DEFAULT_BRANCH	main	Branch for new worktrees
GIT_REMOTE	origin	Git remote name
OPENCODE_BASE_PORT	4096	First port for \fBcoda serve\fR
OPENCODE_PORT_RANGE	10	Ports to scan
DEFAULT_LAYOUT	default	Default tmux layout
CODA_LAYOUTS_DIR	~/.config/coda/layouts	User layout directory
CODA_PROFILES_DIR	~/.config/coda/profiles	User profile directory
CODA_WATCH_INTERVAL	5	Watcher poll interval (seconds)
CODA_WATCH_COOLDOWN	60	Min seconds between repeat notifications
OPENCODE_HEADLESS_PERMISSION	{"*":"allow"}	Permission policy for serve
AUTO_ATTACH_TMUX	true	Auto-attach on SSH login
DEFAULT_TMUX_SESSION	default	Session name for auto-attach
.TE
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.
.SS First-time setup
.EX
\&./install.sh
sudo tailscale up
claude auth login
coda auth
.EE
.
.SS Clone a project and start working
.EX
coda project start --repo git@github.com:user/myapp.git
cd ~/projects/myapp/main
coda
.EE
.
.SS Create a new project from scratch
.EX
coda project start --new my-tool -m "CLI for managing widgets"
.EE
.
.SS Feature branch workflow
.EX
cd ~/projects/myapp/main
coda feature start auth
# ... give OpenCode a task inside the session ...
coda ls
coda switch
coda feature done auth
.EE
.
.SS Apply a layout to a running session
.EX
coda attach myapp--auth
coda layout wide-twopane
coda layout ls
coda layout create my-custom
.EE
.
.SS Running multiple agents in parallel
.EX
cd ~/projects/myapp/main
coda feature start auth
coda feature start payments
coda feature start docs
coda switch          # pick one to check on
.EE
.
.SS Headless background work
.EX
coda serve           # starts on first free port
opencode attach http://localhost:4096
.EE
.
.SS Monitoring sessions for attention
.EX
coda watch               # start the watcher
coda watch status        # check if running
coda watch stop          # stop when done
.EE
.
.SS Sending tasks from the command line (no attach needed)
.EX
tmux send-keys -t coda-myapp--auth \e
    "Add rate limiting to the login endpoint" Enter
tmux capture-pane -t coda-myapp--auth -p | tail -20
.EE
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/coda/shell-functions.sh
Shell functions sourced into bash or zsh.
.TP
.I ~/coda/.env
Local configuration (git-ignored).
.TP
.I ~/coda/.env.example
Configuration template.
.TP
.I ~/coda/layouts/
Built-in tmux layout scripts.
.TP
.I ~/.config/coda/layouts/
User-created tmux layout scripts (override built-ins of the same name).
.TP
.I ~/.config/coda/profiles/
User-created profile files.
.TP
.I ~/coda/completions/coda.bash
Bash tab-completion script.
.TP
.I ~/coda/completions/coda.zsh
Zsh tab-completion script.
.TP
.I ~/.tmux.conf
tmux configuration (installed by
.BR install.sh ).
.TP
.I ~/.config/opencode/tui.json
OpenCode TUI keybind configuration (installed by
.BR install.sh ).
.TP
.I ~/.claude/.credentials.json
Claude Code OAuth credentials (written by
.BR "claude auth login" ).
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
In addition to the
.I .env
variables listed under
.BR CONFIGURATION ,
the following environment variables influence behaviour:
.TP
.B TMUX
If set, indicates the shell is already inside a tmux session.
.B coda
uses
.B switch-client
instead of
.B attach
when this is set.
.TP
.B SSH_CONNECTION
If set (i.e. the shell was started via SSH), and
.B AUTO_ATTACH_TMUX=true
and
.B TMUX
is unset,
.B coda
auto-attaches to
.B DEFAULT_TMUX_SESSION
on shell start.
.
